places.perex: Dress up sporty and spend an afternoon playing golf. Don't forget about beverages.

United Nations Park El Picacho
places.perex: To commemorate the 40th anniversary of United Nations, this park was created. It is in the north of the city covering a big area.

places.name: Santa Lucia
places.perex: A tiny picture-perfect village which is still keeping the traditional Honduran image. Nice walks around.

places.name: Metropolitan Cathedral
places.perex: The cathedral was declared a national monument in 1967 and it is a very popular and important architectural building.

places.name: Archaeological Museum of Comayagua
places.perex: Very intriguing museum which has exhibitions on Mayan history. Numerous excavations and artefacts are on display.

places.name: National Identity Museum
places.perex: Considered to be one of the best museums in the country! Exhibitions on Honduran history and arts.

places.name: Merced Church
places.perex: This historical art piece prides itself with marvellous paintings inside the church and its impressive facade.

places.name: Chiminike Interactive Educational Centre
places.perex: The far-best place for the family! The interactive centre wants to support children in their curiosity and imagination!

places.name: Cerro Juan A. Lainez
places.perex: This huge area covered by woods is a nice place for a walk during hot summer days and also a great jogging spot.

places.name: Plaza Morazan
places.perex: A significant plaza in the city center faces the Metropolitan cathedral. It is a nice laid-back spot.

places.name: La Montañita
places.perex: Hike up this relatively small mountain and admire Tegucigalpa. Take good shoes and your camera.

places.name: Historic Downtown of Tegucigalpa
places.perex: This part of the city is the oldest one. The historical centre has a lot of colonial heritage but is a bit neglected.

places.name: Museum of History of the Republic
places.perex: A very interesting museum which offers an inside look of Honduran history and the creation of the state.

places.name: National Zoo
places.perex: Small zoo worth visiting is located on the Picacho hill. There is a noticeable group of monkeys!

places.name: Presidential House
places.perex: The president of Honduras resides in this mighty building constructed by Augusto Bressani in 1920s. Interesting sight!

places.name: Museum of People of Honduras
places.perex: The Hondurans are really proud of themselves, at least so it seems according to the museums dedicated to them. Honduran paintings!

places.name: Cultural Center of Spain
places.perex: The Spanish centre has a bustling atmosphere. Its cultural events are known all throughout the city and welcome many foreigners also!

places.name: Los Dolores Church
places.perex: Another marvellous architectural gem. This Baroque church decorated by pigeons attracts a lot of attention.

places.name: San Francisco Church
places.perex: One of the oldest churches in Honduras even wins over the age of the Catedral. It is an orange-coloured building with simple design.

places.name: National Gallery of Art
places.perex: Ready for a cultural experience? Then come here and have a blast 'cause the seven rooms will keep you busy and excited all day long!

places.name: Cybex Gym
places.perex: Pump up your muscles in this hi-tech gym! Jog! Sprint!

places.name: La Leona Park
places.perex: The pleasant small park has a good view of downtown and is the nicest place for taking panoramic pictures of the city.

places.name: Museum of Military History
places.perex: If you are interested in weapons, uniforms, military forces, then come to this museum. Free admission!

places.name: Numismatic Museum
places.perex: A numismatic freak or just a casual "money-lover", peep in this museum to see the coins and notes from all over the world!

places.name: Rojo, Verde & Ajo
places.perex: One of the most famous restaurants in the city! A favourite because of its divine cuisine and delightful service!

places.name: Bull Bar
places.perex: Get ready for a long unforgettable night! In this bar you will not notice the time passing.

places.name: Museum of Nature
places.perex: Its exhibitions show the fauna and flora of Honduras. Worth a look are especially those of mammals, reptiles and birds.

places.name: Café Honoré
places.perex: Nice, cosy and laid-back. Something between a bar, café and restaurant. Reasonable prices for very nice meals.

places.name: Valle de Angeles
places.perex: Enjoy walking around in this village which is very close to the national park and therefore you can start off your trip here.

places.name: Mall Plaza Miraflores
places.perex: There is a mighty concentration of high-end labels here, but you can also find some "normal" brand shops here.

places.name: El Carmen Church
places.perex: See this beautiful monumental white washed church in Gothic style. You might get lucky and see a Honduran wedding here!

places.name: Los Próceres Mall
places.perex: The mall is an attractive mix of family-friendly restaurants, cafes, shops. A stroll through this place is a must!

places.name: Cascadas Mall
places.perex: A fully fledged shopping mall sports all kinds of shops, boutiques, restaurants. You can bargain hard here!

places.name: Cinema Aries y Tauro
places.perex: Every day from 7PM there are both Latino-Americano films broadcasted as well as Hollywood blockbusters. A favourite cinema!
